      {
        "id": "https://economic-research.bnpparibas.com/html/en-US/Malaysia-Strong-growth-high-exposure-semiconductor-sector-3/6/2026,53277",
        "title": "Malaysia: Strong growth, high exposure to the semiconductor sector",
        "link": "https://economic-research.bnpparibas.com/html/en-US/Malaysia-Strong-growth-high-exposure-semiconductor-sector-3/6/2026,53277",
        "content": "Malaysia’s economic growth continues to be robust and is projected to remain resilient over the next two years, underpinned by vigorous domestic demand and sustained global consumption of electronic goods. Unlike other ASEAN economies, however, Malaysia has derived little benefit from the decline in Chinese exports to the US market. Moreover, its imports of Chinese products have risen sharply, putting pressure on the manufacturing sector. Like its regional peers, Malaysia is actively expanding its trade and financial partnerships to diversify its exports and attract investment—critical steps to ascending the value chain in artificial intelligence (AI) components.",
        "fullContent": "Malaysia’s economic growth continues to be robust and is projected to remain resilient over the next two years, underpinned by vigorous domestic demand and sustained global consumption of electronic goods. Unlike other ASEAN economies, however, Malaysia has derived little benefit from the decline in Chinese exports to the US market. Moreover, its imports of Chinese products have risen sharply, putting pressure on the manufacturing sector. Like its regional peers, Malaysia is actively expanding its trade and financial partnerships to diversify its exports and attract investment—critical steps to ascending the value chain in artificial intelligence (AI) components.",
