      {
        "id": "https://economic-research.bnpparibas.com/html/en-US/Five-good-reasons-positive-about-Europe-2026-beyond-2/3/2026,53195",
        "title": "Five good reasons to be positive about Europe in 2026 (and beyond)",
        "link": "https://economic-research.bnpparibas.com/html/en-US/Five-good-reasons-positive-about-Europe-2026-beyond-2/3/2026,53195",
        "content": "Europe is getting better and better. It has not been spared shocks, notably the war in Ukraine – its impact on energy prices is largely responsible for German stagnation – and political uncertainty in France, which affected French GDP growth in 2025. But Europe is overcoming these difficulties. GDP Growth in the Eurozone proved robust, at 1.5%, and 2026 should be a positive year, even more than in 2025. Industry has emerged from recession, buoyed by defence, aeronautics and AI, while households are showing purchasing intentions not seen since February 2022. All these factors will help Europe to continue building its strategic autonomy. The context is favourable and Europe is becoming increasingly credible in the eyes of investors.",
        "fullContent": "Europe is getting better and better. It has not been spared shocks, notably the war in Ukraine – its impact on energy prices is largely responsible for German stagnation – and political uncertainty in France, which affected French GDP growth in 2025. But Europe is overcoming these difficulties. GDP Growth in the Eurozone proved robust, at 1.5%, and 2026 should be a positive year, even more than in 2025. Industry has emerged from recession, buoyed by defence, aeronautics and AI, while households are showing purchasing intentions not seen since February 2022. All these factors will help Europe to continue building its strategic autonomy. The context is favourable and Europe is becoming increasingly credible in the eyes of investors.",
        "author": "stephane.colliac@bnpparibas.com",
        "date": "2026-02-02T23:00:00.000Z",
        "image": null
      },
